    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Trim the green stalk off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and cut into quarters, lengthways, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong>\u00a0chopped aubergine</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20 min or until golden and tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the aubergine is roasting, chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add your<strong> fennel seeds</strong> to a<strong> pestle & mortar</strong> and grind to a fine powder</p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle and mortar? Chop them up as finely as you can</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> half</strong> your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until it begins to release some oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>crushed fennel seeds </strong>(not a fan of aniseed? Only add a little!) to the pan\u00a0and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomatoes are beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[400ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are starting to soften, add the <strong>roasted aubergine</strong> and <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy aubergine sauce</strong></p><p>Once boiling, remove the pan from the heat and stir through your <strong>gnocchi</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the contents of the pan<strong> </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or two!)</p><p>Tear over the <strong>remaining 'Nduja </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), top with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy 'Nduja & aubergine gnocchi bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the gnocchi is baking, combine the<strong> remaining balsamic vinegar </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>balsamic dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad </strong>to the<strong> </strong>balsamic dressing and gently mix together</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-gnocchi-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>'Nduja & aubergine gnocchi bake </strong>with the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
